        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 10:05PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1004 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Meade State Park, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beaver, Forgan, Gate, Knowles, Bryans Corner, Baker, Boyd, Mocane,
Turpin, Floris, and Balko.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
